g on interviews, participant-observation, and analysis of websites and tournament documents, Playing Out of Bounds explores how participants understand and negotiate their sense of belonging within this community of volleyball players and how membership within and the boundaries of this community are continually being (re)defined. This identity/community building occurs within a context of anti-Asian racism, growing numbers of mixed race players, and fluidity of what it means to be Canadian, American, Chinese, and Asian.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBelonging (Social psychology). 0aChinese AmericansxEthnic identity. 0aVolleyballxTournamentsxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aVolleyballxTournamentsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh  aAsian American.  aAsian Canadian.  aBiological.  aDiaspora.  aIntersectionality.  aModel.  aRace.  aSport.  aessentialism.  aminority.  aracism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753130040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487531300423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487531300/original  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  